            "pmid": "17984930",
            "title": "Response of ACTH to octreotide in a probable corticotropic adenoma associated with Addison's disease.",
            "abstract": "Our patient was a 65-year-old woman previously diagnosed with Addison's disease. She presented an empty sella turcica and, at the age of 47, was discovered to have autonomous hypersecretion of adrenocorticotropic hormone (ACTH), suggesting a corticotropic adenoma secondary to Addison's disease, with a lack of response to high levels of dexamethasone. She maintained high ACTH levels despite corticosteroid treatment.",
